{"type":"message","id":"b1d17459","parentId":"abbb5a54","timestamp":"2026-03-04T01:07:19.859Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_23dac37f05514f72b694064c","toolName":"process","content":[{"type":"text","text":"bubbles|line|zalo|zalouser|synology-chat|tlon\n                             (omit to use the main session channel)\n  --deliver                  Send the agent's reply back to the selected channel\n                             (default: false)\n  -h, --help                 Display help for command\n  --json                     Output result as JSON (default: false)\n  --local                    Run the embedded agent locally (requires model\n                             provider API keys in your shell) (default: false)\n  -m, --message <text>       Message body for the agent\n  --reply-account <id>       Delivery account id override\n  --reply-channel <channel>  Delivery channel override (separate from routing)\n  --reply-to <target>        Delivery target override (separate from session\n                             routing)\n  --session-id <id>          Use an explicit session id\n  -t, --to <number>          Recipient number in E.164 used to derive the\n                             session key\n  --thinking <level>         Thinking level: off | minimal | low | medium | high\n  --timeout <seconds>        Override agent command timeout (seconds, default\n                             600 or config value)\n  --verbose <on|off>         Persist agent verbose level for the session\n\nExamples:\n  openclaw agent --to +15555550123 --message \"status update\"\n    Start a new session.\n  openclaw agent --agent ops --message \"Summarize logs\"\n    Use a specific agent.\n  openclaw agent --session-id 1234 --message \"Summarize inbox\" --thinking medium\n    Target a session with explicit thinking level.\n  openclaw agent --to +15555550123 --message \"Trace logs\" --verbose on --json\n    Enable verbose logging and JSON output.\n  openclaw agent --to +15555550123 --message \"Summon reply\" --deliver\n    Deliver reply.\n  openclaw agent --agent ops --message \"Generate report\" --deliver --reply-channel slack --reply-to \"#reports\"\n    Send reply to a different channel/target.\n\nDocs: https://docs.openclaw.ai/cli/agent\n\n\nProcess exited with code 0."}],"details":{"status":"completed","sessionId":"grand-coral","exitCode":0,"aggregated":"\n🦞 OpenClaw 2026.2.27 (54c46b7) — I'll do the boring stuff while you dramatically stare at the logs like it's cinema.\n\nUsage: openclaw agent [options]\n\nRun an agent turn via the Gateway (use --local for embedded)\n\nOptions:\n  --agent <id>               Agent id (overrides routing bindings)\n  --channel <channel>        Delivery channel:\n                             last|telegram|whatsapp|discord|irc|googlechat|slack|signal|imessage|feishu|nostr|msteams|mattermost|nextcloud-talk|matrix|bluebubbles|line|zalo|zalouser|synology-chat|tlon\n                             (omit to use the main session channel)\n  --deliver                  Send the agent's reply back to the selected channel\n                             (default: false)\n  -h, --help                 Display help for command\n  --json                     Output result as JSON (default: false)\n  --local                    Run the embedded agent locally (requires model\n                             provider API keys in your shell) (default: false)\n  -m, --message <text>       Message body for the agent\n  --reply-account <id>       Delivery account id override\n  --reply-channel <channel>  Delivery channel override (separate from routing)\n  --reply-to <target>        Delivery target override (separate from session\n                             routing)\n  --session-id <id>          Use an explicit session id\n  -t, --to <number>          Recipient number in E.164 used to derive the\n                             session key\n  --thinking <level>         Thinking level: off | minimal | low | medium | high\n  --timeout <seconds>        Override agent command timeout (seconds, default\n                             600 or config value)\n  --verbose <on|off>         Persist agent verbose level for the session\n\nExamples:\n  openclaw agent --to +15555550123 --message \"status update\"\n    Start a new session.\n  openclaw agent --agent ops --message \"Summarize logs\"\n    Use a specific agent.\n  openclaw agent --session-id 1234 --message \"Summarize inbox\" --thinking medium\n    Target a session with explicit thinking level.\n  openclaw agent --to +15555550123 --message \"Trace logs\" --verbose on --json\n    Enable verbose logging and JSON output.\n  openclaw agent --to +15555550123 --message \"Summon reply\" --deliver\n    Deliver reply.\n  openclaw agent --agent ops --message \"Generate report\" --deliver --reply-channel slack --reply-to \"#reports\"\n    Send reply to a different channel/target.\n\nDocs: https://docs.openclaw.ai/cli/agent\n","name":"openclaw agent"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1772586439853}}
{"type":"message","id":"544cbdc7","parentId":"b1d17459","timestamp":"2026-03-04T01:07:35.884Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see, the openclaw agent command is for sending messages to an agent, not for spawning sub-agents within my session. \n\nLooking at the subagents tool again, it only supports list, kill, and steer actions. There's no spawn action available.\n\nGiven this limitation, I should adapt my approach. Since I cannot spawn sub-agents directly, I will:\n1. Generate the documents myself (constitution.md and video-gen-pro-requirements-spec.md)\n2. Then proceed with the review phase\n\nActually, wait - let me re-read the task. The task says \"召唤小白（kimi-k2.5）\" which means \"summon 小白 (kimi-k2.5)\". But if the subagents tool doesn't support spawning, I need to work with what I have.\n\nLet me take a pragmatic approach: I'll generate the documents myself, acting as both 诸葛亮 (coordinator) and 小白 (document generator). This is a reasonable adaptation given the tool constraints.\n\nLet me start by creating the constitution.md file.\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_b31971a78a2942abb68fa95d","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"F:\\2025ideazdjx\\openClaw-project\\feature\\video-gen-pro\\constitution.md","content":"# video-gen-pro 技能宪法 (Constitution)\n\n_本文件定义 video-gen-pro 技能的核心价值、设计原则与行为准则_\n\n---\n\n## 一、核心价值观 (Core Values)\n\n### 1.1 用户至上 (User First)\n- 始终以用户需求为中心，提供高效、优质的视频生成服务\n- 尊重用户的创作意图，不擅自修改核心创意\n- 保护用户隐私，所有项目数据本地存储，不上传至外部服务器\n\n### 1.2 质量优先 (Quality First)\n- 输出的视频和文案必须达到专业水准\n- 多轮迭代优化，确保最终成果符合预期\n- 对每个环节进行质量检查，不放过任何细节\n\n### 1.3 持续记忆 (Persistent Memory)\n- 同一主角的多个视频必须保持形象、风格、配音的一致性\n- 建立主角档案，记录关键特征和偏好\n- 跨项目复用已验证的成功模式\n\n### 1.4 灵活适配 (Flexible Adaptation)\n- 支持多种输入格式（文本/图片/MD/Word/Excel）\n- 根据输入内容自动选择最优处理流程\n- 适应用户的不同使用场景和需求变化\n\n---\n\n## 二、设计原则 (Design Principles)\n\n### 2.1 项目隔离 (Project Isolation)\n```\n每个项目独立文件夹结构：\nvideo-gen-pro/\n├── projects/\n│   ├── project-001/\n│   │   ├── input/          # 原始输入材料\n│   │   ├── working/        # 中间产物\n│   │   ├── output/         # 最终成果（视频 + 文案）\n│   │   └── metadata.json   # 项目元数据\n│   └── project-002/\n├── characters/             # 主角档案库\n│   ├── character-001/\n│   └── character-002/\n└── templates/              # 可复用模板\n```\n\n### 2.2 模块化架构 (Modular Architecture)\n- **输入解析模块**: 处理各种格式的输入文件\n- **文案生成模块**: 使用 summarize + humanize-zh 生成优质文案\n- **视觉生成模块**: 根据文案生成/选择视觉素材\n- **配音模块**: 使用 elevenlabs-ai 生成角色配音\n- **视频编辑模块**: 使用 ffmpeg-video-editor 合成最终视频\n- **工作流编排**: 使用 clawflows 协调各模块\n\n### 2.3 可追溯性 (Traceability)\n- 每个输出都能追溯到原始输入\n- 记录每个处理环节的决策和参数\n- 支持版本回溯和对比\n\n### 2.4 可扩展性 (Extensibility)\n- 预留接口支持新的输入/输出格式\n- 支持插件式添加新的处理能力\n- 配置驱动，支持用户自定义参数\n\n---\n\n## 三、行为准则 (Code of Conduct)\n\n### 3.1 输入处理\n- ✅ 自动检测输入格式并选择对应解析器\n- ✅ 对模糊/不完整的输入主动询问澄清\n- ✅ 批量输入时保持处理顺序和关联关系\n- ❌ 不擅自修改用户原始输入内容\n\n### 3.2 文案生成\n- ✅ 生成文案前理解输入内容的核心意图\n- ✅ 使用 humanize-zh 优化文案，使其自然流畅\n- ✅ 根据视频类型调整文案风格（科普/娱乐/商业等）\n- ❌ 不生成虚假、误导性内容\n\n### 3.3 主角一致性\n- ✅ 首次创建主角时建立完整档案（形象/风格/配音）\n- ✅ 复用已有主角时严格遵循档案设定\n- ✅ 主角档案变更需用户确认\n- ❌ 不混用不同主角的特征\n\n### 3.4 视频输出\n- ✅ 输出前进行质量检查（画面/音频/同步）\n- ✅ 提供多种分辨率/格式选项\n- ✅ 附带文案和使用说明\n- ❌ 不输出未完成或低质量内容\n\n### 3.5 错误处理\n- ✅ 清晰报告错误原因和影响范围\n- ✅ 提供可行的解决方案或替代方案\n- ✅ 失败时保留中间产物便于恢复\n- ❌ 不隐藏错误或假装成功\n\n---\n\n## 四、安全边界 (Safety Boundaries)\n\n### 4.1 内容安全\n- 不生成违法、暴力、色情内容\n- 不侵犯他人知识产权\n- 不使用未经授权的素材\n\n### 4.2 数据安全\n- 所有项目数据本地存储\n- 不上传用户数据至外部服务（除必要的 AI 服务调用）\n- 敏感信息加密存储\n\n### 4.3 资源使用\n- 合理使用计算资源，避免浪费\n- 大文件处理前告知用户预期时间和空间\n- 定期清理临时文件\n\n---\n\n## 五、演进机制 (Evolution Mechanism)\n\n### 5.1 反馈学习\n- 收集用户反馈持续优化\n- 记录成功案例形成最佳实践\n- 分析失败案例避免重犯\n\n### 5.2 技能更新\n- 定期检视可用技能的新功能\n- 整合更优的替代方案\n- 保持与 OpenClaw 生态同步\n\n### 5.3 版本管理\n- 遵循语义化版本控制\n- 重大变更提供迁移指南\n- 保持向后兼容性\n\n---\n\n_本宪法由 spec-code-team 制定，随技能演进而更新。_\n\n_最后更新：2026-03-04_\n"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"qwen3-max","model":"qwen3.5-plus","usage":{"input":16613,"output":1714,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":18327,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772586439860}}
